AGI - In progress at Palazzo Ferrajoli the meeting 'The Value of Happiness' Remind' on the occasion of the International Day of Happiness. The aim of the initiative is to put this feeling among the priorities for the protection and well-being of people, where they live, operate and transit, and to foster a positive approach - more inclusive, fair and balanced - in relation to personal and professional growth with the aim of sustainable economic and social development.
&nbsp;
Among the participants Maurizio Gasparri president Forza Italia Group to the Senate who declared: "We have lived with Remind many occasions of meeting on technical and economic issues. This moment dedicated to happiness and the well-being of the soul represents a great and new opportunity of reflection to enhance our vision linked to the integral development of the person. We cannot design a sustainable and better world in economic and environmental terms without believing in positive feelings, in healthy human values, anchored to our most authentic traditions. Physical well-being founded on levels of civil cohabitation and within cities and territories increasingly vivable and equipped, with structures and public works able to secure our environments: but not only. We want happy women and men, who realize their projects of life and, at the same time, are adequately protected the most fragile categories, such as elderly, children, disabled or sick. An integral vision of well-being in society, in which everyone can contribute to creating dreams and projects, respecting and enhancing individuality according to principles of sound education and good practices. Each person has the right to conquer his happiness and live fully aspirations and desires, new and better professional dimensions, adequate levels of free coexistence."
&nbsp;
Also present at the meeting Tommaso Foti President Gruppo Fratelli d'Italia at the Chamber. "We must think - it has stated - that we have a nation, a country, which has mainly a vetusto housing patrimony, and especially in this area we have to hypothesize of urban regeneration projects that combine what is a less emission in the atmosphere of Co2, but also the possibility of having green spaces; so we have the need to rethink the cities a little compared to a criterion that was only to expand the city far beyond the traditional borders, there are cities that even quadrupled their extension with respect to the end of the war, we must also realize that if we have to consume less ground, rather than think of extending horizontally, we must also overcome an old heritage that traditionally leads us to have the suspicion for vertical solutions. &nbsp;

