AGI - The official proclamation of the President of the Sardinia Region, Alessandra Todde, and the other 59 regional councillors elected on 25 February last is awaited. The Central Election Office in the Court of Appeal in Cagliari, chaired by President Gemma Cucca, is completing the audits on the eight minutes from the constituency offices at the tribunals of the island, which in the past weeks have worked, in turn, on the minutes arrived from the 1,844 electoral sections of the eight colleges.
&nbsp;
The last, that of Cagliari with its 580 sections, arrived in the Court of Appeal only last Friday at 16.30 and without that - they specify to the AGI&nbsp; from the offices - it would not have been possible to start the final checks. Half an hour after the Central Election Office, chaired by Cucca and formed by two other magistrates, one secretaries and five experts. began calculations for the definitive allocation of seats. According to the complex mechanism provided for by the disputed electoral law of Sardinia in 2013 (one of the main causes of the delays of the iter), the votes must first be assigned to the president candidates, the simplest to calculate since a simple algebraic sum is necessary. The estimated deviation between Todde and the opponent of Paolo Truzzu is - according to sources of the wide field - of more than three thousand votes.
&nbsp;
<
Then the central electoral office allocates seats, with quotient and with the remains, to the individual lists and therefore, among the candidates who have obtained the greatest number of preferences. Once the operations have been completed, the Office in the Court of Appeal shall forward the outcome to the General Secretariat of the Regional Council and the Presidency of the Regional Council.
