AGI - The European elections, the relations with the Quirinale, the Perugia investigation into the dossier against vip and political representatives, the fight against tax evasion. Giorgia Meloni, interviewed by Agorà on Raitre, addresses the hot themes of the moment, starting from the June vote, and draws a budget of what has been done so far by his government. To the Europeans "for me a victory would confirm the result that brought me a year ago to the government - confesses the premier -. It will not be easy but it is the goal to which point. I would give up the leadership of the nation when I realized that I no longer have the consent of the Italians. I couldn't do it anymore if I didn't have the freedom to do it, the freedom to hack, I'm not here to survive."
&nbsp;
On relations with the head of the state that in recent weeks have been defined by many observers as a confrontation, instead, Meloni is clear: "I&nbsp;miei relations with President&nbsp;Mattarella&nbsp; they are excellent, never fails its support not to the government but to the nation. Ours is a relationship that we manage directly and personally and those that brigany to ruin it will be disappointed".&nbsp;The reform of the premier, he explains, "will come into force in any case in the next legislature, predictably in 2028" when "it is not granted" that Giorgia&nbsp;Meloni&nbsp;sia at Palazzo Chigi and when the mandate of Sergio&nbsp;Mattarella "The reform does not concern me nor Mattarella, it does not concern the present but the future of the nation and it is on this that the Italians will be called to decide."
&nbsp;
On the case of dossiers, the premier says "more than worried very outraged. On this story we have to go all the way, I think there have been power groups that have taken advantage of for their own interests, we have to go all the way to discover the responsible and the mandates". As for the centre-left, he adds, "I do not allow myself to give advice to Elly&nbsp;Schlein; over the years I have seen a left engaged in the demonization of opponents while politics should be respect for the opponent, not fight in the mud. I respect for &nbsp;Schlein&nbsp; so I hope that on that side of the barricade you will make a change on this."
&nbsp;
Other topical issue, taxes: "The left has indignated - remembers Meloni - because I said that the taxes are not a beautiful thing and I confirm it, the liberal donations are beautiful, the levies imposed by law are not a beautiful thing and for greater reason just because they are not a beautiful thing you have to use at the best the proceeds of that taxation. I do not accept, as I have heard, the leader of the PD saying that health, which is paid with taxes, is beautiful: I agree but give lessons also no because it was this government to bring the health fund to its historical maximum." The premier also responds to his government's accusation of being "friend of evaders": "2023 was the record year in the recovery of tax evasion - clarifies -, the Revenue Agency has cashed 25 billion 4.5 billion more than the previous, never recorded numbers: Now if we who made these numbers are friends of the evaders who was there before us and did not do them what should be?. Having a fisco friend means having a fisco that does not oppress families and enterprises with destroyed rules and with an unsustainable level of taxation that does not correspond to the level of services that with the proceeds of that taxation are issued, a fisco friend is what asks you to pay the right taxes and that it claims that you do it with sustainable times and that does not use the proceeds of that taxation for useless things but uses them with a principle with a principle of principle". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
Speaking of the economic health of our country, the premier says: "We currently have a record of employment, a record of stable contracts. The OECD says that in Italy the average real income has increased while elsewhere it decreased, Istat says that the risk of poverty has decreased and we have the record of Italian state bonds required on foreign markets but also the great result of the Btp value, for small savers, which has collected 53 billion in three issues. It is a very important thing for me because we have to put much of the Italian debt back in Italian hands. Oggettively Italy is giving a good proof of itself".&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Finally, a joke also on the G7: "It is a great opportunity because it allows us to put on the table of our partners our priorities, it is the opportunity for Italy to guide the scheme, it is an extraordinary commitment but I think it gives extraordinary fruits." concludes Meloni.
